message.content:
cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on Content Delivery Networks (CDNs) and caching algorithms for delivering content over the Internet. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes two TTL-based caching algorithms and provides provable guarantees for content request traffic that is bursty and non-stationary. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with designing algorithms that adapt to the heterogeneity and non-stationary nature of real-world content requests. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as CDNs play a crucial role in delivering secure content over the Internet, and caching algorithms can impact the security of the content. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is also a possible category as the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed algorithms using a large-scale trace from a production CDN server.
